TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gompers, Paul A.
AU  - Metrick, Andrew
T1  - Institutional Investors and Equity Prices*
PY  - 2001
Y1  - 2001/02/01
DO  - 10.1162/003355301556392
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 116
IS  - 1
SP  - 229
EP  - 259
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper analyzes institutional investors' demand for stock characteristics and the implications of this demand for stock prices and returns. We find that “large” institutional investors nearly doubled their share of the stock market from 1980 to 1996. Overall, this compositional shift tends to increase demand for the stock of large companies and decrease demand for the stock of small companies. The compositional shift can, by itself, account for a nearly 50 percent increase in the price oflarge-company stock relative to small-company stock and can explain part of the disappearance of the historical small-company stock premium.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1162/003355301556392
ER  - 



